# Endpoint and state map

## Auth requirements (web/server.py)

- **Unauthed**: `GET /api/parts`, `POST /api/preview`, `GET /api/preview/temp/*`, all static files, `GET /` (index)
- **JWT required**: `POST /api/render`, `POST /profile/{userhash}/config/{name}`, `DELETE /profile/{userhash}/config/{name}`
- Profile ownership enforced: JWT `user_nicename` must match URL `userhash`

## State locations

- **S3 (durable, shared)**: `configs/{cfghash}`, `profiles/{userhash}`, `render/{cfghash}/bundle.zip`
- **Local process (ephemeral, per-instance)**: `_position_cache` dict in server.py, JWT token cache in auth.py, preview temp STLs in `output/preview_temp/`

## Multi-instance implication

Preview POST writes STLs to local disk; the follow-up GET may hit a different instance and 404. Fix options: return STL bytes inline, upload to S3, or use sticky sessions.
